{"id": 223760490, "title": "RFK Jr. Accepts Chance for Libertarian Party's Presidential Nomination", "text": "Robert F. Kennedy Jr. will now be a candidate for the Libertarian Party's presidential nomination.Kennedy, an independent presidential candidate who spoke at the convention Friday, was nominated Sunday by a delegate at the party's convention in Washington, DC.After his nomination, Kennedy submitted a video to the convention that was played in front of the delegates at the Washington Hilton. He stated:\"I accept this unexpected honor, I've always admired the Libertarian Party, I have a deep alignment with the core values, the antipathy towards war, a commitment to end the addiction to forever wars and the love of personal freedoms and liberties. The constitution was written for hard times, there are no exceptions. I'm going to protect the United States Constitution, I'm going to end the foreign wars. I'm very grateful to the libertarian party for this great honor.\"Prior to the national convention, delegates were selected by state Libertarian affiliates. These delegates will choose a party nominee Sunday at the convention by majority vote.This is a developing news story that will be updated with more information.", "summary": "In a video sent to the convention, Kennedy said, \"I accept this unexpected honor, I've always admired the Libertarian Party.\"", "url": "https://www.newsweek.com/robert-kennedy-jr-rfk-will-candidate-libertarian-party-presidential-nomination-1904839", "image": "https://d.newsweek.com/en/full/2398451/robert-f-kennedy-jr.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-26 16:26:52", "author": "Gabe Whisnant", "authors": ["Gabe Whisnant"], "language": "en", "source_country": "US", "sentiment": 0.298}